5
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:33,380
Daddy, do you know what I saw?

6
00:04:33,450 --> 00:04:36,890
It was the most fantastic thing.
Come look.

7
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,890
My son.

8
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:42,050
Look, son,
I'm really busy...

9
00:04:42,130 --> 00:04:45,660
but I'll tell you
what I do need.

10
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:47,890
I need some good luck.

11
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:59,230
[Horse Panting]

12
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:25,860
[Panting Continues]

13
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:39,300
[Sniffing]

14
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:50,250
[Horse Chewing]

15
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:57,320
[Horse Snorting]

16
00:07:57,390 --> 00:08:01,230
[Snorting, Whinnying]

17
00:08:04,770 --> 00:08:08,500
[Speaking Arabic]

18
00:08:41,470 --> 00:08:45,100
[Horse Snorting]

19
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:49,970
[Horse Whinnies, Stomps]

20
00:08:58,450 --> 00:09:03,050
[Father] Okay, Mr. Lucky,
it's time we divvy up the loot.

21
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:07,790
Look at all of these things.
What a night. [Laughing]

22
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:12,730
What do you think of this?
This is pretty. I'll take those.

23
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,170
Try that.
Isn't that pretty?

24
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:18,030
I better keep that.
That's pretty nice.

25
00:09:18,110 --> 00:09:20,900
I think I better take that.
You shouldn't have that.

26
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:27,240
I better take that.
You're too young for that.

27
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,680
Look at that watch.

28
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:31,680
I'll take that.
That's a pretty watch.

29
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:39,950
It's time I got myself another knife.
So I ought a give you this.

30
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:43,330
You never know when a knife
might come in handy.

31
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,360
You want some gold?
There's lots of gold.

32
00:09:56,710 --> 00:10:01,200
You know, I'll bet this is
the most valuable piece here.

33
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:05,410
It's Bucephalus, the magic horse
of Alexander the Great.

34
00:10:05,490 --> 00:10:09,820
A long time ago, this king
was gonna kill Bucephalus...

35
00:10:09,890 --> 00:10:13,120
because he was so wild
the king couldn't ride him.

36
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:16,930
He had Bucephalus brought
into a big arena.

37
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:20,300
People came from all around.

38
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:23,390
They wanted to see this horse
that was the biggest...

39
00:10:23,470 --> 00:10:28,000
and the blackest and the strongest,
most beautiful horse that ever was.

40
00:10:28,070 --> 00:10:31,910
King Philip walked out there
and looked at some of his men.

41
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:34,740
He said, 'Kill that horse.'

42
00:10:34,810 --> 00:10:38,080
Just then a voice called out
from the edge of the crowd.

43
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:40,750
It said, 'I can ride that horse.'

44
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:45,590
Everybody said, 'Who said that? '

45
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:51,490
It was a little kid, just about
your size, just about your age.

46
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,930
King Philip said...

47
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:59,770
'Son, if you can ride that horse,
you can have that horse.'

48
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,540
So Alexander walked out
into the big arena.

49
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:09,710
Standing in the middle of the arena
was Bucephalus.

50
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:12,840
He was big, and he was strong.

51
00:11:14,190 --> 00:11:17,160
He was pawing the ground...

52
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:19,890
and there was fire in his eyes...

53
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:22,550
and there was smoke
coming out of his nose.

54
00:11:22,630 --> 00:11:24,290
He went...
[Snorting]

55
00:11:25,970 --> 00:11:27,730
Alexander walked up...

56
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,070
then quick as a cat,
he jumped up on his back.

57
00:11:30,140 --> 00:11:33,400
He grabbed hold
of that long, black mane...

58
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:35,170
and away they went,
like lightning.

59
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:38,730
He jumped right over the crowd,
over the stand...

60
00:11:38,810 --> 00:11:41,410
and went riding' out
over the hill.

61
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:45,080
Everybody said, 'Whew! '

62
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:50,720
Smoke coming' out of his nose!

63
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:52,660
[Snorting]

64
00:11:52,730 --> 00:11:54,420
Fire in his eyes.

65
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:56,260
Fire in his eyes!

66
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:58,390
That's the way I heard the story.

67
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,330
Here. I want you
to have this.

68
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:09,900
Bucephalus.

69
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:15,310
[Wind Howling]

70
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:19,320
(music)(music) [Flute Playing]

71
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:25,220
[Waves Crashing]

72
00:12:25,290 --> 00:12:28,920
[Ship Creaking]

73
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:34,190
(music)(music) [Playing Flute]

74
00:12:56,690 --> 00:12:59,620
[Ship Creaking]

75
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:08,020
[Muffled Explosion]

76
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,310
Dad, what's going on?

77
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:21,370
- Ow!
- Alec!

78
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:24,850
- Alec, come here!
- [Explosion]

79
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,810
[Woman Screaming]

80
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:31,190
Just take it easy.
We'll be okay.

81
00:13:32,090 --> 00:13:34,250
- What's happening?
- I don't know. Put this on.

82
00:13:34,330 --> 00:13:37,060
Help me with this. Here.
Come here, son.

83
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:38,790
Put this life vest on.

84
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:41,030
It's okay.
Tie the bottom.

85
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:44,960
[Father Groaning]

86
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:50,740
[Ship Creaking Loudly]

87
00:13:50,810 --> 00:13:52,740
Let's get out of here!

88
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:01,380
[Passengers Shouting]

89
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:05,390
[Screaming]

90
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:13,090
