131
00:45:28,900 --> 00:45:34,740
[Fire Crackling]

132
00:46:36,370 --> 00:46:38,530
[Alec Shouts]

133
00:46:38,610 --> 00:46:43,540
[Men Speaking Italian]

134
00:46:55,620 --> 00:46:59,560
- [Speaking Italian]
- [Alec Whistles]

135
00:47:01,830 --> 00:47:05,730
[Speaking Italian]

136
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:18,010
[Speaking Italian]

137
00:47:24,850 --> 00:47:28,380
- [Speaking Italian]
- [Horse Whinnying]

138
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:36,120
[Speaking Italian]

139
00:47:36,200 --> 00:47:39,030
He saved my life.

140
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:41,500
I can't leave the island
without him.

141
00:47:41,570 --> 00:47:45,200
- [Speaking Italian]
- He'll die without me.

142
00:47:49,080 --> 00:47:52,810
[Horse Whinnying]

143
00:47:52,880 --> 00:47:55,870
- [Speaking Italian]
- [Alec Screaming]

144
00:47:58,550 --> 00:48:01,750
- [Alec Shouting]
- [Whinnying]

145
00:48:01,820 --> 00:48:03,480
[Alec]
Stop!

146
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:24,010
[Alec]
Let me go!

147
00:48:26,680 --> 00:48:30,640
[Men Speaking Italian]

148
00:48:30,720 --> 00:48:32,020
[Alec] Black!

149
00:48:36,790 --> 00:48:39,090
Black, come on!

150
00:48:42,130 --> 00:48:46,290
[Men Speaking Italian]

151
00:48:53,340 --> 00:48:54,900
Black!

152
00:48:56,810 --> 00:48:58,680
[Shouting In Italian]

153
00:50:09,350 --> 00:50:12,380
'Ode to Alec Ramsey.'

154
00:50:12,450 --> 00:50:15,220
'I think that I shall never see...

155
00:50:15,290 --> 00:50:20,320
a boy as brave as Alec Ramsey.

156
00:50:20,400 --> 00:50:23,960
Hunger and thirst,
in fear and pain.

157
00:50:24,030 --> 00:50:26,690
He lived because
his heart had aim.

158
00:50:26,770 --> 00:50:30,330
A horse
as black as night to day...

159
00:50:30,410 --> 00:50:33,070
a beast, a god...

160
00:50:33,140 --> 00:50:36,470
with whom he did stay.

161
00:50:36,540 --> 00:50:39,740
They slept on the sand
and played in the ocean.

162
00:50:39,810 --> 00:50:43,750
And rode over the island
in a singular motion.

163
00:50:43,820 --> 00:50:47,910
Now, here he sits,
a hero among boys...

164
00:50:47,990 --> 00:50:53,760
with the love of a horse,
much more than mere toys.'

165
00:51:31,700 --> 00:51:33,790
[Horse Snorts]

166
00:51:44,980 --> 00:51:47,000
[Sighs]

167
00:52:37,130 --> 00:52:41,570
[Yawning]

168
00:53:00,490 --> 00:53:02,320
[Door Closes]

169
00:53:32,950 --> 00:53:35,890
I'm very happy
to have my son back.

170
00:53:37,690 --> 00:53:42,290
Thank you. I wish you could have
saved his father too.

171
00:53:49,470 --> 00:53:51,730
[Mrs. Ramsey Sighs]

172
00:53:52,810 --> 00:53:55,740
You're kind of a pretty horse.

173
00:54:08,320 --> 00:54:12,880
[Truck Approaching, Brakes Squeak]

174
00:54:12,960 --> 00:54:17,690
[Banging]

175
00:54:17,760 --> 00:54:20,390
[Clattering]

176
00:54:20,470 --> 00:54:22,770
[Black Snorts]

177
00:54:27,070 --> 00:54:28,940
[Snorts]

178
00:54:31,910 --> 00:54:34,940
- [Snorting]
- What...

179
00:54:35,020 --> 00:54:37,920
- [Whinnies]
- [Man Screams]

180
00:54:39,690 --> 00:54:43,590
[Whinnying, Screaming Continue]

181
00:54:43,660 --> 00:54:45,090
Black, no!

182
00:54:46,830 --> 00:54:50,590
[Cans Clattering, Men Screaming]

183
00:54:50,660 --> 00:54:54,960
[Horn Honking]

184
00:54:58,370 --> 00:54:59,500
No!

185
00:55:00,910 --> 00:55:03,340
Black, come back!

186
00:55:09,850 --> 00:55:11,180
Alec!

187
00:55:27,970 --> 00:55:31,930
[Brakes Screech, Man Shouting]

188
00:55:36,040 --> 00:55:37,980
[Horns Honking]

189
00:55:41,520 --> 00:55:42,980
[Man Gasps]

190
00:55:46,320 --> 00:55:48,190
Wow!

191
00:55:50,020 --> 00:55:52,720
Yes, I saw a black horse!
It ran that away!

192
00:56:08,040 --> 00:56:10,370
[Factory Whistle Blowing]

193
00:56:14,110 --> 00:56:16,050
[Boat Whistle Blowing]

194
00:56:48,880 --> 00:56:52,580
[People Talking, Laughing]

195
00:56:52,650 --> 00:56:55,050
[Horns Honking]

196
00:57:17,940 --> 00:57:20,880
[Approaching Hoof beats]

197
00:57:20,950 --> 00:57:24,750
[Hoof beats Continue]

198
00:57:44,440 --> 00:57:45,870
Whoa.

199
00:57:51,180 --> 00:57:53,540
What happened to you?

200
00:57:56,180 --> 00:57:58,880
- Everything.
- Everything?

201
00:57:58,950 --> 00:58:00,940
That's a whole lot.

202
00:58:01,020 --> 00:58:02,960
Can't be everything.

203
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:12,560
You lost a black horse.

204
00:58:15,540 --> 00:58:18,400
Yeah. Have you seen him?

205
00:58:18,470 --> 00:58:21,410
Do you know where he is?

206
00:58:23,610 --> 00:58:26,240
- Napoleon...
- [Napoleon Snorts]

207
00:58:26,310 --> 00:58:29,440
Did you tell me
you saw a black stallion?

208
00:58:29,520 --> 00:58:31,510
[Neighs Softly]

209
00:58:34,320 --> 00:58:37,020
[Napoleon Sighs]

210
00:58:40,190 --> 00:58:42,660
Well, what did he say?

211
00:58:44,330 --> 00:58:47,600
He says,
'Well, not very far from here.'

212
00:58:49,400 --> 00:58:52,270
Just past the dairy...

213
00:58:52,340 --> 00:58:55,870
there's a big black barn.

214
00:58:55,940 --> 00:58:59,280
Then you see a long bunch
of skinny trees...

215
00:58:59,350 --> 00:59:00,870
that you walk around.

216
00:59:00,950 --> 00:59:05,610
Then you go right by a morning star.

217
00:59:05,690 --> 00:59:08,150
You keep following that star...

218
00:59:08,220 --> 00:59:12,160
and see a large patch
of green grass.

219
00:59:12,230 --> 00:59:13,690
Then you stop.

220
00:59:13,760 --> 00:59:15,750
Then you listen.

221
00:59:15,830 --> 00:59:19,860
Pretty soon you'll see
just what you've been looking for.

222
00:59:27,240 --> 00:59:29,170
[Yawns]

223
00:59:30,940 --> 00:59:35,070
[Whinnying In Distance]

224
00:59:35,150 --> 00:59:38,780
[Whinnying Continues]

225
00:59:43,420 --> 00:59:44,860
Hey, Black!

226
01:00:08,820 --> 01:00:10,110
Black?

227
01:00:30,070 --> 01:00:32,660
[Banging]

228
01:00:51,990 --> 01:00:55,480
- [Cat Yowls]
- [Wings Fluttering]

229
01:01:03,400 --> 01:01:05,670
[Footsteps Approaching]

230
01:01:05,740 --> 01:01:07,230
[Screams]

231
01:01:08,810 --> 01:01:11,040
[Whinnying, Snorting]

232
01:01:11,110 --> 01:01:12,200
Black!

233
01:01:15,550 --> 01:01:18,040
Black, it's you!

234
01:01:21,490 --> 01:01:24,360
[Muttering]

235
01:01:24,420 --> 01:01:27,290
You okay?
I knew it was you.

236
01:01:27,360 --> 01:01:31,660
- [Footsteps Approaching]
- [Door Unlatching]

237
01:01:37,700 --> 01:01:40,640
[Footsteps Descending Stairs]

238
01:01:46,610 --> 01:01:48,670
What do you think
you're doing' over there, sonny?

239
01:01:48,750 --> 01:01:51,840
I'm getting' my horse!

240
01:01:53,390 --> 01:01:55,320
[Metal Clattering]

241
01:02:01,430 --> 01:02:03,760
You're a big, fat thief!

242
01:02:06,000 --> 01:02:08,060
- Nobody's a thief.
- You are!

243
01:02:08,140 --> 01:02:10,570
I said, 'Nobody's a thief.'

244
01:02:12,170 --> 01:02:15,870
Who do you think you're calling' a thief?
This is my place.

245
01:02:15,940 --> 01:02:17,910
I'm thinking' that's my horse.

246
01:02:17,980 --> 01:02:21,280
No, he's mine!

247
01:02:21,350 --> 01:02:25,180
Hold on, son.
Wait a minute.

248
01:02:28,360 --> 01:02:31,120
- What are you gonna do here, buddy?
- [Horse Snorting]

249
01:02:33,190 --> 01:02:35,130
What are you gonna do?

250
01:02:40,130 --> 01:02:41,570
[Snorting]

251
01:02:43,740 --> 01:02:45,170
Easy.

252
01:02:59,090 --> 01:03:02,250
Maybe he is yours...

253
01:03:02,320 --> 01:03:06,880
but I spent all last night trying'
to catch this wild horse.

254
01:03:06,960 --> 01:03:08,890
All night I spent.

255
01:03:15,070 --> 01:03:18,200
You're just lucky I got him
instead of the police.

256
01:03:18,270 --> 01:03:19,700
Hear me?

257
01:03:24,540 --> 01:03:27,670
[Man Chuckling]
He kicked a garbage man?

258
01:03:29,120 --> 01:03:31,180
He's something', all right.

259
01:03:31,250 --> 01:03:33,190
Did you have any breakfast?

260
01:03:47,500 --> 01:03:51,060
Henry, I think
he likes it out here.

261
01:04:03,880 --> 01:04:07,680
[Henry]
Tried cows. It didn't work.

262
01:04:09,920 --> 01:04:12,390
5:00 in the morning.

263
01:04:12,460 --> 01:04:13,720
Chickens...

264
01:04:16,460 --> 01:04:19,760
They just about drove me nuts.
[Chuckles] Chickens.

265
01:04:19,830 --> 01:04:25,700
Look, if you clean this stall up
in here real good...

266
01:04:25,770 --> 01:04:29,330
and you get it fit for him,
I could let you have it.

267
01:04:52,770 --> 01:04:54,960
[Turns Key, Engine Churns]

268
01:04:57,470 --> 01:04:59,560
[Churning Continues]

269
01:05:07,210 --> 01:05:09,080
[Sighs]

270
01:05:09,150 --> 01:05:12,740
[Engine Starts, Revs]

271
01:08:01,860 --> 01:08:04,880
There are too many red cards.

272
01:08:12,900 --> 01:08:15,490
Is The Black fast?

273
01:08:15,570 --> 01:08:17,500
He's fast.

274
01:08:19,040 --> 01:08:21,410
Fast enough
to be a racehorse?

275
01:08:24,280 --> 01:08:27,080
That Black is a desert horse.

276
01:08:27,150 --> 01:08:29,480
He's fast, all right.
Sure, he's fast.

277
01:08:31,020 --> 01:08:33,380
But he hasn't got any papers.

278
01:08:33,450 --> 01:08:36,390
Fast or not, I don't think
they'd ever let him run.

279
01:08:39,490 --> 01:08:42,260
Can I ask you a question?

280
01:08:42,330 --> 01:08:44,060
Sure.

281
01:08:44,130 --> 01:08:47,160
Why did you stop training?

282
01:08:53,340 --> 01:08:55,270
I got tired.

283
01:09:06,490 --> 01:09:10,650
Do you think you'll ever
try it again?

284
01:09:17,730 --> 01:09:19,200
Sure, I do.

285
01:09:21,530 --> 01:09:22,870
Sure.

286
01:09:31,080 --> 01:09:32,510
It's work.

287
01:09:33,710 --> 01:09:36,340
Worth it, though.

288
01:09:40,090 --> 01:09:43,280
Hold onto him good, son.
Stay in the centre of him.

289
01:09:43,360 --> 01:09:45,520
Turn him around the other way.

290
01:09:45,590 --> 01:09:49,190
The other way, son.
Bring him in and turn him around.

291
01:09:49,260 --> 01:09:51,420
Now send him down around here.

292
01:10:17,690 --> 01:10:19,120
[Whinnies]

293
01:10:35,040 --> 01:10:37,370
[Sighs]

294
01:10:45,250 --> 01:10:50,660
(music)(music) [Fanfare]

295
01:10:54,090 --> 01:10:57,150
[Reporter] It comes as no surprise
that again this week...

296
01:10:57,230 --> 01:11:00,220
both Sunraider,
the fiery red stallion from the West...

297
01:11:00,300 --> 01:11:02,600
and Cyclone,
the sleek gray from the East...

298
01:11:02,670 --> 01:11:04,860
have won their races with ease.

299
01:11:04,940 --> 01:11:08,270
They have won
with monotonous regularity.

300
01:11:08,340 --> 01:11:12,610
But, hey-hey,
let's see these two champions...

301
01:11:12,680 --> 01:11:14,440
run head-to-head.

302
01:11:14,510 --> 01:11:18,010
Perhaps horse fans will be treated
to the match race of the century.

303
01:11:18,080 --> 01:11:22,610
This is 'Hey-Hey' Jim Neville,
from Belmont.

304
01:11:24,960 --> 01:11:28,120
Looking' this way.
Not looking' down on the ground.

305
01:11:28,190 --> 01:11:30,960
Looking' straight ahead.
That's right.

306
01:11:31,030 --> 01:11:33,620
[Grunting]

307
01:11:33,700 --> 01:11:36,000
You want to see what's coming',
you look underneath your arm.

308
01:11:37,100 --> 01:11:39,630
Not over your shoulder.
Down under here.

309
01:11:39,710 --> 01:11:44,300
In here. See what's going on
down there, all around you.

310
01:11:44,380 --> 01:11:47,210
You can scoot and boot,
understand?

311
01:11:47,280 --> 01:11:50,310
Then you've got your balance.

312
01:11:52,720 --> 01:11:55,810
Keep your knees in close
when you're putting' your stirrups on.

313
01:11:55,890 --> 01:12:00,760
Check down underneath here too.
Get that leather out of your way.

314
01:12:00,830 --> 01:12:04,190
Pull it back in there underneath
so that your knees...

315
01:12:04,260 --> 01:12:07,100
Nothing' in the way in here.
All right.

316
01:12:07,170 --> 01:12:11,100
Now you're up. Feel that?
Feel that in your legs?

317
01:12:11,170 --> 01:12:14,610
Hmm? Feel it pulling'
on your legs back here?

318
01:12:14,670 --> 01:12:16,110
- Mm-hmm.
- All right.

319
01:12:16,180 --> 01:12:19,270
Look ahead down the lane.

320
01:12:19,350 --> 01:12:21,870
No, you don't jump
straight up and down.

321
01:12:21,950 --> 01:12:24,440
Just try and keep your body
as still as possible.

322
01:12:24,520 --> 01:12:28,210
He'll be moving'.
He'll be making' that rhythm.

323
01:12:28,290 --> 01:12:32,280
You just go on with him.
You don't have to pump him.

324
01:12:32,360 --> 01:12:35,790
Just kind of go
straight ahead with him.

325
01:12:35,860 --> 01:12:38,960
Just like you're throwing it away,
like this.

326
01:12:39,030 --> 01:12:42,090
Throw it away.
That's right.

327
01:12:42,170 --> 01:12:43,860
Throw it away.
That's right.

328
01:12:45,200 --> 01:12:48,800
When a horse starts out of that gate,
you've got to remember this.

329
01:12:48,880 --> 01:12:52,740
Remember, you don't want him
to outbreak you.

330
01:12:52,810 --> 01:12:55,140
You know what that means?
That horse starts to settle...

331
01:12:55,210 --> 01:12:58,810
They open that gate, wham, like that.

332
01:12:58,890 --> 01:13:01,410
Some of 'em just scat!

333
01:13:01,490 --> 01:13:03,720
You can't do that,
so you grab a handful of mane...

334
01:13:03,790 --> 01:13:06,590
just before he says, 'Go,'
so he don't outbreak you.

335
01:13:06,660 --> 01:13:11,260
Because they'd open that gate,
and you'd just be sitting' in mid-air.

336
01:13:11,330 --> 01:13:13,590
You understand?

337
01:13:13,670 --> 01:13:16,260
- This Black can outbreak you.
- Right.

338
01:13:16,340 --> 01:13:18,460
He can move right on out there.

339
01:14:38,650 --> 01:14:40,850
[Henry]
You know, Alec...

340
01:14:42,360 --> 01:14:43,790
'secrecy.'

341
01:14:45,390 --> 01:14:47,120
That's the key word.

342
01:14:49,130 --> 01:14:50,890
Yeah. Okay.

343
01:14:50,960 --> 01:14:53,450
Don't just say, 'Okay.'
Know what I'm talking about.

344
01:14:53,530 --> 01:14:58,630
It's a secret.
You and me, we have a secret.

345
01:15:20,690 --> 01:15:24,090
[Henry] Now, listen to me.
We'll just make this an easy workout.

346
01:15:24,160 --> 01:15:25,600
- You understand?
- All right.

347
01:15:25,670 --> 01:15:29,600
Get him used to this place.
Jake and I will be here with Napoleon.

348
01:15:29,670 --> 01:15:32,760
You go down to the half-mile pole
and watch me.

349
01:15:32,840 --> 01:15:34,860
I'll give you the start
by dropping my hand.

350
01:15:34,940 --> 01:15:38,430
Then I want you to work him
for a half mile.

351
01:15:38,510 --> 01:15:40,950
I want to you to breeze him
for a half mile...

352
01:15:41,010 --> 01:15:42,610
then pull him up, nice and easy.

353
01:15:42,680 --> 01:15:45,880
Go down to the half-mile pole
and watch me.

354
01:16:27,660 --> 01:16:29,560
Come on! Let's go!

355
01:16:52,680 --> 01:16:54,950
[Alec Grunting]

356
01:16:58,360 --> 01:17:00,520
Too much horse for your boy.

357
01:17:13,500 --> 01:17:16,370
Jake, he's gonna be all right.

358
01:17:28,650 --> 01:17:31,250
Hyah. Come on, Nappy.
Let's go.

359
01:17:44,900 --> 01:17:46,670
- [Whinnies]
- Whoa.

360
01:17:59,220 --> 01:18:03,150
[Henry]
Come on! Giddap! Go on, get him!

361
01:18:03,220 --> 01:18:05,690
Pull him up!

362
01:18:06,790 --> 01:18:09,880
Pull him up, Nappy!
On the inside!

363
01:18:15,430 --> 01:18:17,060
Come on, Jake.

364
01:18:23,970 --> 01:18:25,410
[Snorts]

365
01:18:25,480 --> 01:18:29,240
[Henry]
Hey, your hand's... You all right?

366
01:18:29,310 --> 01:18:31,110
I'm okay.

367
01:18:32,180 --> 01:18:34,410
[Alec]
I better walk him now.

368
01:18:34,480 --> 01:18:37,420
All right, go ahead.
Cool him out, son.

369
01:18:43,330 --> 01:18:44,760
[Jake Chuckles]

370
01:18:44,830 --> 01:18:47,090
Did you get what I got?

371
01:18:49,500 --> 01:18:52,260
- [Jake Chuckles]
- Right on the button.

372
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:58,440
That horse has got speed
he ain't even tapped yet.

373
01:19:03,280 --> 01:19:04,870
You're not...

374
01:19:06,950 --> 01:19:10,390
You're not actually...
You're not.

375
01:19:10,450 --> 01:19:12,450
You are out of your mind.

376
01:19:12,520 --> 01:19:16,720
That monster has no more business
being out on this track with class...

377
01:19:16,790 --> 01:19:18,730
- [Henry Laughs]
- He's fast, but he's wild.

378
01:19:18,800 --> 01:19:21,390
You saw him zigzagging
all over the course.

379
01:19:21,470 --> 01:19:23,730
[Henry Grunts]

380
01:19:23,800 --> 01:19:26,060
What about his papers?

381
01:19:29,970 --> 01:19:33,430
- He ain't got any.
- He ain't?

382
01:19:33,510 --> 01:19:35,740
That's taste.

383
01:19:35,810 --> 01:19:39,300
What are you gonna do?
Hitch him up to a plough?

384
01:19:39,380 --> 01:19:40,650
No.

385
01:19:43,150 --> 01:19:44,620
I got an idea.

386
01:19:51,330 --> 01:19:53,090
A match race?

387
01:19:53,160 --> 01:19:55,260
Cyclone?

388
01:19:55,330 --> 01:19:57,770
You are too much.

389
01:19:57,830 --> 01:20:00,430
You are really too much.
[Chuckling]

390
01:20:00,500 --> 01:20:03,440
You got me thinking crazy too.

391
01:21:24,920 --> 01:21:27,650
Squeeze my hand.
I want to try something here.

392
01:21:27,720 --> 01:21:29,780
You feel that?
That's a pretty good grip.

393
01:21:29,860 --> 01:21:34,130
That's not bad, but we're gonna
have to work on your grip.

394
01:21:34,200 --> 01:21:38,130
What I used when I was a rider
was this ball. See how...

395
01:21:38,200 --> 01:21:40,800
- What does a ball do?
- It strengthens your band.

396
01:21:40,870 --> 01:21:45,310
No matter what you're doing'
through the day, just use this ball.

397
01:21:45,380 --> 01:21:49,900
Let me see you do it. Next time you
grip my hand, we'll see a difference.

398
01:21:49,980 --> 01:21:53,380
[Neville On Radio] This reporter has
the hottest racing news of the year.

399
01:21:53,450 --> 01:21:54,880
Hold onto your hats.

400
01:21:54,950 --> 01:21:57,320
The most sensational
match race imaginable...

401
01:21:57,390 --> 01:22:00,550
between Cyclone from the East
and Sunraider from the West...

402
01:22:00,620 --> 01:22:03,750
is finally set for the afternoon
of August 15 at Santa Anita.

403
01:22:03,830 --> 01:22:06,820
They'll go over two gruelling miles
to prove once and for all...

404
01:22:06,900 --> 01:22:09,090
which is really
the greatest champion.

405
01:22:09,170 --> 01:22:12,830
This is 'Hey-Hey' Jim Neville
from Belmont.

406
01:22:35,430 --> 01:22:39,290
[Henry]
Well, whoever you are...

407
01:22:39,360 --> 01:22:41,300
here we go.

408
01:23:10,290 --> 01:23:13,260
(music)(music) [Humming]

409
01:23:17,000 --> 01:23:18,800
[Knocking]

410
01:23:21,840 --> 01:23:23,740
It's open.

411
01:23:23,810 --> 01:23:27,770
(music)(music) [Humming Continues]

412
01:23:39,320 --> 01:23:42,490
Sure is quiet in here today.

413
01:23:42,560 --> 01:23:44,620
Anything wrong with that?

414
01:23:46,200 --> 01:23:48,130
The Black, he...

415
01:23:50,800 --> 01:23:53,130
He just wouldn't play.

416
01:23:53,200 --> 01:23:57,970
He just stands there
and looks out into the rain.

417
01:23:58,040 --> 01:23:59,800
[Clears Throat]

418
01:23:59,880 --> 01:24:02,570
[Man]
Maybe The Black is blue today.

419
01:24:02,650 --> 01:24:05,110
- Did you ever think of that?
- 'Blue'?

420
01:24:05,180 --> 01:24:08,510
[Chuckles]
Rain, man, rain.

421
01:24:08,590 --> 01:24:09,880
Rain.

422
01:24:12,990 --> 01:24:14,420
[Clears Throat]

423
01:24:14,490 --> 01:24:18,430
We're gonna show everybody that he's
the fastest horse in the world.

424
01:24:22,170 --> 01:24:24,430
You think you know that animal?

425
01:24:24,500 --> 01:24:26,440
Yeah, I know him.

426
01:24:29,670 --> 01:24:31,370
I don't know.

427
01:24:33,480 --> 01:24:34,910
[Man Sighs]

428
01:24:36,180 --> 01:24:38,240
I get a funny feeling.

429
01:24:40,120 --> 01:24:46,020
I feel right now that you better
let that horse stay wild, Alec.

430
01:24:50,360 --> 01:24:52,450
It's his soul.

431
01:24:56,700 --> 01:25:01,670
[Thunder Rumbling]

432
01:25:01,800 --> 01:25:05,400
[Snorting]

433
01:25:05,470 --> 01:25:08,740
[Thunder Rumbling]

434
01:25:15,480 --> 01:25:18,280
- [Whinnies]
- Easy, Black.

435
01:25:56,690 --> 01:25:59,960
- He ain't gonna show.
- I don't wanna hear that.

436
01:26:00,030 --> 01:26:03,490
He'll show. He'll be here.

437
01:26:05,370 --> 01:26:06,800
[Alec Sighs]

438
01:26:08,400 --> 01:26:11,070
[Jake]
He probably doesn't even remember us.

439
01:26:11,140 --> 01:26:15,740
- He'll be here.
- We're ancient history.

440
01:26:15,810 --> 01:26:18,910
I tell you, he's gonna be here.
He's busy.

441
01:26:18,980 --> 01:26:20,510
[Alec]
He's a little jumpy.

442
01:26:22,750 --> 01:26:24,910
- [Thunderclap]
- [Whinnying]

443
01:26:24,990 --> 01:26:27,250
Come on. We'll work him.
Get him out there.

444
01:26:33,660 --> 01:26:37,190
- [Thunderclap]
- [Whinnying]

445
01:26:37,270 --> 01:26:38,490
[Alec] Henry!

446
01:26:38,570 --> 01:26:41,430
- [Alec] You okay?
- [Jake] Where'd he get you?

447
01:26:41,500 --> 01:26:44,270
- On my arm.
- [Jake] Here?

448
01:26:44,340 --> 01:26:46,500
- [Jake] Is it broken?
- [Henry] Leave it alone!

449
01:26:46,580 --> 01:26:48,510
It's all right.
He just nicked me.

450
01:26:48,580 --> 01:26:50,940
Will you please stop?

451
01:26:51,010 --> 01:26:53,950
All right. What?

452
01:26:57,250 --> 01:26:58,690
It's him.

453
01:27:04,290 --> 01:27:06,560
- It's him.
- [Jake] No.

454
01:27:06,630 --> 01:27:11,070
[Henry] It's him, by God.
I tell you, it's him.

455
01:27:16,140 --> 01:27:18,070
[Jake]
It is him.

456
01:27:23,650 --> 01:27:26,620
Yeah. All right. It's him.

457
01:27:33,490 --> 01:27:37,430
[Henry]
All right. Give him a leg up there.

458
01:27:40,630 --> 01:27:43,100
Remember, this is our big chance.

459
01:27:43,170 --> 01:27:45,330
It's up to you.

460
01:27:45,400 --> 01:27:47,430
Take him out.

461
01:28:22,300 --> 01:28:24,200
Come on! Bring him on!

462
01:28:44,030 --> 01:28:45,930
[Hoof beats]

463
01:28:46,000 --> 01:28:47,830
[Stopwatch Ticking]

464
01:29:01,880 --> 01:29:04,470
[Hoof beats Approaching]

465
01:29:04,550 --> 01:29:09,180
[Stopwatch Ticking]

466
01:29:10,790 --> 01:29:16,050
[Hoof beats Approaching]

467
01:29:43,890 --> 01:29:46,620
[Henry]
Hey! He's out cold.

468
01:29:46,690 --> 01:29:49,060
- He passed out.
- [Black Panting]

469
01:29:50,460 --> 01:29:54,090
Get him out of that mane.
Hold him steady.

470
01:29:54,160 --> 01:29:55,930
- [Jake] Got him.
- [Henry] Give me your knife.

471
01:29:56,000 --> 01:29:59,930
- [Jake] All right.
- [Henry] Watch it. Hold him steady.

472
01:30:00,000 --> 01:30:01,590
[Jake] Whoa, sonny.

473
01:30:01,670 --> 01:30:05,110
[Henry Groans, Mutters]
Here.

474
01:30:18,090 --> 01:30:22,520
- Where'd you get this animal?
- [Henry] Get him off.

475
01:30:22,590 --> 01:30:25,420
- [Henry Groans]
- [Jake] Good boy.

476
01:30:25,490 --> 01:30:27,930
- [Henry] Get him out of here.
- [Jake] I got him.

477
01:30:28,000 --> 01:30:30,630
Watch yourself.
Watch it, sir.

478
01:30:30,700 --> 01:30:33,290
- [Black Snorts]
- [Jake] Whoa, boy.

479
01:31:00,330 --> 01:31:02,920
What happened?
Did I fall off?

480
01:31:04,270 --> 01:31:05,560
No.

481
01:31:05,630 --> 01:31:09,430
No, you hung on like a champ.

482
01:31:20,350 --> 01:31:23,050
What happened?
Where's The Black?

483
01:31:23,120 --> 01:31:25,780
It's all right.
Don't worry about it. It's fine.

484
01:31:25,850 --> 01:31:28,150
He's over in the van with Nappy.

485
01:31:35,030 --> 01:31:38,120
He did good, didn't he?

486
01:31:38,200 --> 01:31:39,670
[Henry] He did great.

487
01:31:39,740 --> 01:31:41,670
You did great.

488
01:31:44,840 --> 01:31:46,810
[Henry] You all right?

489
01:31:57,390 --> 01:32:01,550
- How did you like what you saw?
- I wasn't disappointed.

490
01:32:02,320 --> 01:32:04,260
[Henry] Disappointed?

491
01:32:04,330 --> 01:32:07,920
You never saw a horse
run like that in your life.

492
01:32:08,000 --> 01:32:10,060
This could put you back
in the action, eh, Dailey?

493
01:32:11,670 --> 01:32:16,230
Don't get hard with me.
You know I never liked it.

494
01:32:16,310 --> 01:32:17,740
I need this race.

495
01:32:18,970 --> 01:32:21,440
I need it bad,
and you can do it.

496
01:32:24,510 --> 01:32:26,980
Will you do it?

497
01:32:27,050 --> 01:32:29,110
If that horse goes like that
with a kid...

498
01:32:29,180 --> 01:32:32,750
- what will he do with a real rider?
- [Henry] The race.

499
01:32:33,860 --> 01:32:35,520
Nice going, kid.
You got guts.

500
01:32:49,740 --> 01:32:51,900
[Neville On Radio] You heard me say
that Cyclone and Sunraider...

501
01:32:51,970 --> 01:32:53,970
are the fastest horses
in the world today.

502
01:32:54,040 --> 01:32:57,530
I'm going to eat those words now
because I've seen another horse...

503
01:32:57,610 --> 01:33:00,410
that defies the imagination,
that runs like a demon possessed...

504
01:33:00,480 --> 01:33:03,080
at night, alone,
at speeds beyond belief.

505
01:33:03,150 --> 01:33:05,590
He's never run a race,
and he comes out of nowhere...

506
01:33:05,650 --> 01:33:09,090
but he could be the greatest
sensation in racing history.

507
01:33:09,160 --> 01:33:11,520
So I challenge the owners
of both Cyclone...

508
01:33:11,590 --> 01:33:16,760
and Sunraider to meet this mystery horse
in their upcoming match race.

509
01:33:16,830 --> 01:33:18,490
This isn't a joke.

510
01:33:18,570 --> 01:33:21,930
This mystery horse is real,
and I'll stake my reputation on it.

511
01:33:22,000 --> 01:33:25,440
This is 'Hey-Hey' Jim Neville
from Belmont.

512
01:33:30,350 --> 01:33:34,710
Do you know any
real good, famous jockeys?

513
01:33:34,780 --> 01:33:39,120
There are a lot of 'em.
George Wolf, the Iceman.

514
01:33:39,190 --> 01:33:42,780
That's just what they call him.
Georgie Wolf.

515
01:33:42,860 --> 01:33:45,290
They call him in the newspapers
the Iceman...

516
01:33:45,360 --> 01:33:48,120
because he sits chilly
on a horse.

517
01:33:48,200 --> 01:33:50,290
That means he sits there
and he can wait.

518
01:33:50,370 --> 01:33:52,630
He knows what to do.
He's studying a horse.

519
01:33:52,700 --> 01:33:56,970
He's up there riding',
going' on with him.

520
01:33:57,040 --> 01:33:59,630
You know what I mean?
He's sitting' up there, going' on...

521
01:33:59,710 --> 01:34:01,730
just studying' him!

522
01:34:01,810 --> 01:34:05,580
Studying' him.
Just studying' him.

523
01:34:05,650 --> 01:34:08,080
When it's time to make his move...

524
01:34:08,150 --> 01:34:10,910
he'll say...
[Whistles, Snaps Finger, Sighs]

525
01:34:10,990 --> 01:34:13,560
Here comes the Iceman!
[Laughs]

526
01:34:30,910 --> 01:34:34,840
Mum, do you want me
to mow the lawn...

527
01:34:34,910 --> 01:34:37,440
or wash the dishes
or something?

528
01:34:41,650 --> 01:34:43,080
Sure.

529
01:34:43,150 --> 01:34:47,610
Why don't you make all the beds
and vacuum in here too?

530
01:34:47,690 --> 01:34:49,120
[Mother Coughs]

531
01:35:10,650 --> 01:35:14,050
- Mum, have you read this here? See?
- What is it?

532
01:35:17,790 --> 01:35:20,190
This is more about that mystery horse.

533
01:35:21,260 --> 01:35:22,690
Boy.

534
01:35:28,900 --> 01:35:33,770
Remember last year when they were
giving away aluminium ballpoint pens?

535
01:35:33,840 --> 01:35:36,360
- The Black is the mystery horse.
- It's amazing the lengths...

536
01:35:36,440 --> 01:35:41,430
they will go to get people
to go to a horse race.

537
01:35:41,510 --> 01:35:43,670
And I'm gonna ride him.

538
01:35:43,750 --> 01:35:45,810
- [Doorbell Rings]
- I'll get it!

539
01:35:45,880 --> 01:35:48,350
[Mrs. Ramsey]
What did you say? Wait!

540
01:35:48,420 --> 01:35:52,790
Alec, wait one more second.
What did you say? Say that again.

541
01:35:52,860 --> 01:35:55,790
The Black is the mystery horse,
and I'm gonna ride him.

542
01:35:55,860 --> 01:35:58,690
[Sighs] Alec, that horse
is not the mystery horse.

543
01:35:58,760 --> 01:36:01,820
Even if he were,
you're not gonna ride him.

544
01:36:01,900 --> 01:36:04,490
It was a secret.
I told you as soon as I could.

545
01:36:04,570 --> 01:36:07,730
You're not supposed to keep
secrets from your mother.

546
01:36:07,800 --> 01:36:10,070
[Sighs]

547
01:36:10,140 --> 01:36:13,070
- Someone's at the door.
- I know!

548
01:36:15,140 --> 01:36:18,080
- Mrs. Ramsey, how...
- Oh.

549
01:36:18,150 --> 01:36:22,810
The Black is the mystery horse,
and you're gonna ride him in a race.

550
01:36:27,320 --> 01:36:31,590
All right. Well, well, well.

551
01:36:31,660 --> 01:36:34,250
Isn't this just fascinating timing?

552
01:36:34,330 --> 01:36:37,090
What's been going on
between you two guys and that horse?

553
01:36:37,170 --> 01:36:40,600
- I have a right to know.
- Guess you've been talking to Alec.

554
01:36:40,670 --> 01:36:45,110
I have been trying to. Would you like
to tell me something about this?

555
01:36:45,170 --> 01:36:48,110
- I'd be happy to.
- Come in, please.

556
01:36:48,180 --> 01:36:53,950
It's quite a long story,
Mrs. Ramsey.

557
01:36:55,020 --> 01:36:57,450
I'm sure it's a long story.

558
01:36:57,520 --> 01:37:00,490
But you've got to be kidding,
thinking I'll let him ride in a race.

559
01:37:00,560 --> 01:37:03,720
My son could get killed
in a horse race.

560
01:37:03,790 --> 01:37:06,730
[Henry] I think you
could be exaggerating.

561
01:37:06,800 --> 01:37:10,060
I'm not exaggerating.
Don't lie to me, Mr. Dailey.

562
01:37:10,130 --> 01:37:14,070
You're willing to risk his life?
I'm not willing to risk his life.

563
01:37:14,140 --> 01:37:17,570
I've lost a husband,
and I'm not gonna lose a son.

564
01:37:17,640 --> 01:37:22,910
[Henry] I wouldn't hurt that boy
for anything in the world.

565
01:37:22,980 --> 01:37:26,910
[Mrs. Ramsey] What kind of dreams
are you filling his head with?

566
01:37:26,980 --> 01:37:31,580
It's much more than just a race.

567
01:37:31,650 --> 01:37:35,420
Your son has his heart set on it.

568
01:37:37,830 --> 01:37:41,090
Good-bye, Mr. Dailey.

569
01:37:41,160 --> 01:37:43,100
Good-bye, Mrs. Ramsey.

570
01:37:43,170 --> 01:37:45,930
[Door Opens, Closes]

571
01:37:54,840 --> 01:37:56,780
[Mrs. Ramsey Sighs]

572
01:38:02,120 --> 01:38:05,880
So what happened to the new deal,
the clean slate?

573
01:38:07,790 --> 01:38:10,050
[Sighs]

574
01:38:10,130 --> 01:38:14,560
Alec, I can't let you
ride in that horse race.

575
01:38:14,630 --> 01:38:16,560
It's ridiculous.

576
01:38:20,500 --> 01:38:21,940
I'm sorry.

577
01:38:34,820 --> 01:38:36,280
What is that?

578
01:38:37,990 --> 01:38:40,580
Alexander the Great's horse.

579
01:38:55,840 --> 01:38:57,930
Dad gave it to me...

580
01:38:59,610 --> 01:39:01,700
just before the storm.

581
01:39:11,450 --> 01:39:17,220
It reminds me
of The Black and me.

582
01:39:19,660 --> 01:39:25,070
Alexander's father gave it to him...

583
01:39:25,130 --> 01:39:27,070
before he died.

584
01:39:32,980 --> 01:39:37,410
I was in the water.

585
01:39:37,480 --> 01:39:39,810
I couldn't breathe.

586
01:39:39,880 --> 01:39:43,080
It was dark and...

587
01:39:43,150 --> 01:39:44,580
I...

588
01:39:49,830 --> 01:39:52,420
I yelled out for Dad, but...

589
01:39:55,500 --> 01:40:01,090
I looked up,
and there was The Black...

590
01:40:01,170 --> 01:40:03,760
and I grabbed onto him.

591
01:40:03,840 --> 01:40:05,970
He saved your life, didn't he?

592
01:40:21,690 --> 01:40:23,120
Oh, Alec.

593
01:40:27,530 --> 01:40:30,360
What am I gonna do?

594
01:40:37,440 --> 01:40:39,460
I gotta ride.

595
01:41:04,330 --> 01:41:05,770
Okay, Alec.

596
01:42:10,500 --> 01:42:13,630
[Jockey]
Neville planned the publicity?

597
01:42:13,700 --> 01:42:16,640
I'll bet the mystery horse
don't even show.

598
01:42:19,840 --> 01:42:22,440
Did you see that?

599
01:42:24,010 --> 01:42:26,280
I'll beat him.

600
01:42:27,850 --> 01:42:31,650
- I heard Mendoza's coming' in.
- Who's missing from the room?

601
01:42:31,720 --> 01:42:35,160
- That beats him right there.
- Yeah. Who rides him?

602
01:42:35,220 --> 01:42:37,620
Where did that guy over there
get them silks?

603
01:42:37,690 --> 01:42:41,560
- Looks like he's ready for Halloween.
- It sure does.

604
01:42:46,900 --> 01:42:48,960
Rider number one, up.

605
01:42:54,140 --> 01:42:58,310
- Number one, sir.
- Add two pounds.

606
01:42:58,380 --> 01:43:00,240
Got that, George?

607
01:43:11,230 --> 01:43:13,190
Rider number two now.

608
01:43:16,300 --> 01:43:17,730
Thank you.

609
01:43:19,000 --> 01:43:20,930
Rider number three.

610
01:43:25,740 --> 01:43:28,370
Number three?
Number three?

611
01:43:28,440 --> 01:43:29,880
How do I look?

612
01:43:29,940 --> 01:43:32,110
Number three, please.

613
01:43:32,180 --> 01:43:34,740
I don't think he's gonna show.
It's been a joke.

614
01:43:34,820 --> 01:43:37,580
[Muttering]

615
01:43:48,860 --> 01:43:53,230
[Chuckles] The mystery rider.
Hop on the scale.

616
01:43:53,300 --> 01:43:57,140
- He's not strong enough to go two miles.
- No way. Too small.

617
01:43:57,210 --> 01:44:01,200
- Rider on the scale, please.
- He's on the scale, sir.

618
01:44:01,280 --> 01:44:03,140
He's on the scale?

619
01:44:05,980 --> 01:44:07,410
Add it on.

620
01:44:19,660 --> 01:44:23,600
[Crowd Clapping]

621
01:45:33,000 --> 01:45:35,470
Okay. All right.

622
01:45:37,510 --> 01:45:41,530
Take him out.
All right, bring him right on out.

623
01:45:49,850 --> 01:45:54,480
[Playing 'Call To Post']

624
01:46:12,410 --> 01:46:17,110
[Crowd Cheering]

625
01:46:19,580 --> 01:46:23,070
[Track Announcer] Two miles.
They'll come by the stands twice.

626
01:46:23,150 --> 01:46:24,620
The stands are jammed.

627
01:46:24,690 --> 01:46:29,520
[Announcer Continues, Indistinct]

628
01:46:58,620 --> 01:47:00,050
[Gate Shuts]

629
01:47:31,850 --> 01:47:34,250
He's moving on the black horse,
the mystery horse.

630
01:47:40,330 --> 01:47:42,090
Bring that horse.

631
01:47:58,980 --> 01:48:02,680
- [Gate Shuts]
- [The Black Whinnies, Snorts]

632
01:48:05,620 --> 01:48:07,180
Cyclone, settle! Whoa!

633
01:48:53,830 --> 01:48:55,270
[Bell Rings]

634
01:49:00,010 --> 01:49:01,570
Whoa!

635
01:49:03,710 --> 01:49:05,510
Stop, Black!

636
01:49:07,110 --> 01:49:09,170
There's some problem
with the mystery horse.

637
01:49:35,110 --> 01:49:37,580
Cyclone keeping the pace.

638
01:50:06,470 --> 01:50:08,440
They're in the front turn now.

639
01:52:40,700 --> 01:52:45,600
[Crowd Cheering]

640
01:52:53,910 --> 01:52:56,470
He's won!
The mystery horse won!

641
01:53:09,320 --> 01:53:11,790
This, ladies and gentlemen...

642
01:53:50,360 --> 01:53:55,130
This horse has got a leg like iron.
It's gonna be all right, son.

643
01:53:58,070 --> 01:53:59,330
Henry!

644
01:57:16,070 --> 01:57:17,330
}}


